 from jgoss gaia torolab ibm com jeff goss subject re changing brake fluid is it necessary in reply to lcarr gmuvax gmu edu s message of two three apr nine three one six three one two nine zero five zero zero lines one five organization ibm toronto lab in article lcarr gmuvax gmu edu writes hi i ve been seeing all these articles about changing brake fluid and i am wondering if this is really necessary i have an eight six toyota corolla sr five with nine four zero zero zero and i am in the only if you want to stop seriously though every two years you should have this done brake fluid absorbs water over time the water becomes steam when the fluid gets hot and steam compresses you ll also have better luck with the longevity of master cylinder calipers and brake lines jeff goss